Following the decision by the Federal Government to suspend all sporting activities over the COVID-19 pandemic, the Organizers of the annual FCV Gladiator Camp, a football clinic, has postponed the clinic which was earlier scheduled to hold between April 5 to 10 in Lagos and April 12 to 17 in Abuja. In a statement signed by one of the organizers, Oluseyi Oyebode, the postponement becomes necessary as the health of the participants are very important. “The Federal Government has suspended all sporting activities and as a law-abiding body, we want to follow the law of the land and that is why we have decided to postpone the camp to July 2020. The Lagos leg of the camp will be hosted by Grange School in Ikeja, while Aduvie International School will host the Abuja camp of the one-week football clinic,” Oyebode said.